          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-1" n="1">My Pedagogue Dear I read with surprise</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-2" n="2">Your long sorry Rhymes which You made on My Eyes</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-3" n="3">As the Dean of S<hi rend="superscript">ṭ</hi> Patrick's sayes, Earth, sea, and skies!</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-4" n="4">I cannot Lye down but immediately rise</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-5" n="5">To Answer Your stuff, and the Doctor's likewise.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-6" n="6">Like a horse with a Gall I am pester'd with Flies</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-7" n="7">But his head and his Tayl new succour supplies</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-8" n="8">To Beat off the Vermin, from Back, Rump, and Thighs.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-9" n="9">The Wing of a Goose before me now lies,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-10" n="10">Which is both shield and sword for such Weak Enemies.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-11" n="11">Whoever opposes me certainly dies,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-12" n="12">Tho' he Were as Valiant as Conde or Guise.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-13" n="13">The Women disturb me a Crying of Pies</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-14" n="14">With Voice twice as loud as a horse when he neighs,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-15" n="15">By this S<hi rend="superscript">ṛ</hi> you find shou'd we Rhyme for a Prize</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-H300CWJS-line-16" n="16">That I'd gain Cloath of Gold when You'd scarce merit Frize.</l>
          </lg>
